The paper discusses the challenges of identifying and training predictive models for large datasets, which is a common problem in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The proposed solution involves advanced model search techniques and resource allocation, which are key components of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses physical optimization via batching, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
